SvMonitorAttr.label: Client Properties File
SvMonitorAttr.description: custom client properties file. For WebSphere 5.x+, you should select an appropriate soap.client.props file. <WebSphereDir>/properties/soap.client.props will be used by default.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Password
SvMonitorAttr.description: the password for login to WebSphere server

SvMonitorAttr.label: Port Number
SvMonitorAttr.description: the port number of WebSphere server (SOAP port for WebSphere 5+, default is 8880)

SvMonitorAttr.label: Security Realm
SvMonitorAttr.description: security realm for WebSphere server (3.5x only).

SvMonitorAttr.label: Server
SvMonitorAttr.description: the name of the server without the backslashes

SvMonitorAttr.label: Target
SvMonitorAttr.description: the logical name of the server. If empty, the hostname will be used.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Timeout
SvMonitorAttr.description: timeout in seconds

SvMonitorAttr.label: User Name
SvMonitorAttr.description: the username for login to WebSphere server

SvMonitorAttr.label: WebSphere Directory
SvMonitorAttr.description: Enter path to WebSphere Directory. This directory should contain at least an Admin Console installation.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Version
SvMonitorAttr.description: version of WebSphere server

SvMonitorAttr.label: Counters
SvMonitorAttr.description: Current selection of counters.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Password
SvMonitorAttr.description: the password for the URL

SvMonitorAttr.label: Port
SvMonitorAttr.description: port number on server - default is 80 for non-secure & 443 for secure

SvMonitorAttr.label: Refresh Selected Metrics Frequency
SvMonitorAttr.description: how often to tell server which metrics we want to monitor.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Proxy Server
SvMonitorAttr.description: the name of the proxy server server if needed

SvMonitorAttr.label: Proxy Password
SvMonitorAttr.description: the password for the proxy server

SvMonitorAttr.label: Proxy Username
SvMonitorAttr.description: the username for the proxy server

SvMonitorAttr.label: Secure Server
SvMonitorAttr.description: check here if server is secure

SvMonitorAttr.label: Hostname
SvMonitorAttr.description: the name of the server

SvMonitorAttr.label: Target
SvMonitorAttr.description: the logical name of the server. If empty, the hostname will be used.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Timeout
SvMonitorAttr.description: the time out, in seconds, to wait for the response

SvMonitorAttr.label: Servlet URL
SvMonitorAttr.description: URL of Performance Servlet. On a WAS 4.0 server, the default URL is /wasPerfTool/servlet/perfservlet. On earlier versions, the URL is chosen during the installation of the Servlet. In either case, the URL can be found in the Servlet properties page on the Admin Console.

SvMonitorAttr.label: User
SvMonitorAttr.description: the username for the URL

SvMonitorAttr.label: Don't use in Templates
SvMonitorAttr.description: this is the path to the log file. However, it should not be used, because it is not loaded all of the time. It depends on the state of the monitor

SvMonitorAttr.label: Run Alerts
SvMonitorAttr.description: How alerts for this monitor are triggered by the following options: (1) For 'for each log entry matched and report status' the monitor triggers alerts for every matching entry found based on the Error If and Warning If thresholds defined for the monitor. (2) For 'once, after all log entries have been checked', the monitor counts up the number of matches and then triggers alerts based on the Error If and Warning If thresholds defined for the monitor.

SvMonitorAttr.label: EMS Configuration File Path
SvMonitorAttr.description: the path to the EMS integration configuration file.

SvMonitorAttr.label: EMS Time Difference
SvMonitorAttr.description: Time difference between the EMS and the SiteView machines.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Server
SvMonitorAttr.description: the server to monitor

SvMonitorAttr.label: Content Match
SvMonitorAttr.description: enter the text to match in a log entry or a regular expression. By default successful match makes monitor alert or error.

SvMonitorAttr.label: No Error on File Not Found.
SvMonitorAttr.description: if the file is not found then don't error.

SvMonitorAttr.label: Check from Beginning
SvMonitorAttr.description:
Select file checking option as follows:
Never - Check only newly added records (default)
First Time Only - Check the whole file once, then only new records
Always - Always check the whole file

SvMonitorAttr.label: Rules File Pathname
SvMonitorAttr.description: optional, pathname to a custom rules file, used instead of Content Match (for example C:/SiteView/classes/CustomMonitor/examples/sample.rules

SvMonitorAttr.label: Match Value Labels
SvMonitorAttr.description: Labels for the values matched on the script output, separated by a ","

SvMonitorAttr.label: WhatsUp installation Directory
SvMonitorAttr.description: Directory where whatsup is installed
